# Shopping list design — nf4lm

---

## Overview

The shopping list is a first-class entity. Recipes contribute ingredients to
it but do not own it. All changes are incremental — the list is never rebuilt
from scratch.

Two list contexts exist:
- Personal: belongs to a single user
- Household: shared by all members of a household, one per household

Both follow identical behavior unless noted otherwise.

---

## Item structure

```json
{
  "id": "uuid",
  "name": "string",
  "normalized_name": "string",
  "quantities": [{ "qty": "string", "unit": "string" }],
  "checked": false,
  "checked_by": "user_id | null",
  "source_recipes": ["recipe_id"],
  "optional": false,
  "secret": false,
  "assigned_to": ["user_id"],
  "substitutions": [{ "qty": "string", "unit": "string", "name": "string" }],
  "substituted_with": "string | null",
  "item_order": 0
}
```

- `quantities` — array of qty/unit pairs. All unit entries for the same
  ingredient are stored together in this array regardless of unit type.
  Displayed joined with " + ".
- `checked_by` — user_id of the member who checked the item. Null if unchecked.
  Displayed in the household list to indicate who checked it off.
- `source_recipes` — array of recipe IDs that contributed this item.
  Empty array for manually added items.
- `secret` — item is only visible to the sharing owner of the source recipe.
  Marked with a visual symbol in the list. Hidden entirely from other members.
- `assigned_to` — array of user IDs. Empty means unassigned. Any member can
  assign or reassign any item — not restricted to the owner.
- `substituted_with` — name of substitution chosen, null if none.

---

## Adding items

### Adding a recipe
- Each ingredient is normalized and checked against existing items
- Match found (fuzzy, Levenshtein 1, min 4 chars for fuzzy, exact for shorter):
  quantities merged into the quantities array, source_recipes updated,
  substitutions union-merged
- No match: new item created
- Optional flag: stays true only if ALL contributing ingredients are optional
- Range quantities: upper bound used when merging qty

### Adding manually
- Input parsed using the ingredient parser
- Normalized and checked against existing items
- Match: quantities merged into existing item
- No match: new item created
- Manual items have an empty source_recipes array

### Ingredient select (partial recipe add)
- User selects a subset of a recipe's ingredients
- Same merge logic as full recipe add
- Only selected ingredients contribute to source_recipes

---

## Removing items

### Removing a recipe from the list
- For each ingredient in the removed recipe, find the matching list item
- Subtract the recipe's qty contribution from the quantities array
- Remove the recipe ID from source_recipes
- If quantities is empty and source_recipes is empty: remove item entirely
- If the user had manually edited the qty of an affected item, show a prompt
  with three options:
  1. Remove the recipe's qty contribution from the item
  2. Keep the current qty as-is
  3. Remove the ingredient entry entirely

### Removing a manually added item
- If source_recipes is also empty: remove item entirely
- If item also has recipe sources: subtract manual contribution, keep item

### Clear Done
- Deletes all checked items from the list entirely

### Clear All
- Deletes all items and resets all source tracking
- Confirm dialog before proceeding

---

## Checking items

- Any member can check or uncheck any item
- checked_by is set to the user_id of whoever checked it, cleared on uncheck
- In household lists, the alias of the member who checked an item is shown
  on the item row
- Checked items displayed below unchecked items with a visual divider
- Checked items: reduced opacity, strikethrough on qty and name

---

## Qty editing

- User can tap the qty of any unchecked item to edit inline
- Edited qty is saved directly to the item
- If the item has multiple quantity entries, editing replaces the entire
  quantities array with the new parsed value

---

## Substitutions

- Items with substitutions show a chevron — tapping opens a modal
- Modal shows substitutions as interactive rows with circular checkboxes
- Tapping a substitution: marks item checked, sets substituted_with,
  sets checked_by, shows "Using: X" toast

---

## Copy bar

- Two buttons: Simple copy and Copy with measurements
- Simple copy: name only for all unchecked items
- Copy with measurements: "qty unit name" per line for all unchecked items
- Both copy unchecked items only
- Toast "Nothing to copy" if all items are checked

---

## Item display

- Unchecked items shown above checked items regardless of item_order
- Visual divider between unchecked and checked sections
- Each item always shows all recipe source pills — one pill per source recipe,
  showing the recipe title. No item ever shows a "combined" label instead.
- Item shows "using: X" if substituted_with is set
- Item shows "optional" note if optional and not substituted
- Secret items marked with a consistent visual symbol throughout the app
- In household lists: checked items show the alias of the member who checked them
- Empty state with prompt to add a recipe or item

---

## Normalization and merging

- Normalize: lowercase, strip punctuation, collapse whitespace, strip leading
  articles (a/an/the), singularize
- Singularization: hardcoded irregulars + rules for -ies/-ves/-es/-s
- Fuzzy match: Levenshtein distance 1, minimum 4 characters — shorter names
  require exact match
- All units for the same ingredient stored as separate entries in the
  quantities array

---

## Household list specifics

- Shared by all members — any member can add, remove, check, assign items
- Any member can Clear Done or Clear All
- Item assignment: any member can assign or reassign any item to any number
  of members
- Secret ingredients from shared recipes: visible only to the sharing owner,
  marked with a visual symbol, hidden entirely from other members
- When a shared recipe is unshared, its contributed items are removed using
  the same recipe removal logic above

---

## SSE

- Personal list: shopping_changed event sent to the owning user only
- Household list: shopping_changed event sent to all household members
